---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="The Orthotic Retail Trap: What Works vs. Gimmicks | Practical Podiatrist">
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 text-slate-300 relative z-10">
    <header class="mb-12 border-b border-white/10 pb-8">
      <span class="text-xs font-bold text-accent uppercase tracking-widest block mb-2">Consumer Protection Guide</span>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white mb-4">Exposing the Orthotic Price Trap</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-400">A 25-year clinical autopsy on multi-thousand-dollar retail gimmicks and cheap pharmacy foam traps.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="space-y-8 text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed">
      <p>Do not spend thousands on generic retail mall inserts (like the Good Feet Store) stamped onto flat pads. Avoid flimsy drugstore foam inserts (like Dr. Scholl's) that collapse in days. Use the "Twist Test" in the store aisle: if an insert bends easily or folds like a soft taco, it will fail your body weight. Look for a firm polypropylene sub-shell.</p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
